22/07/2009
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- Police and customs officers on Tuesday (July 21st) seized a large heroin shipment at the Danube Bridge checkpoint on the Bulgarian-Romanian border, media reported.
In a joint operation by the State Security Agency, border police and the Customs Agency, officers found 62.5kg of heroin in a van driven by a Bulgarian national, believed to be part of an international drug-trafficking ring.
(BTA, BNR, Focus, Sofia Echo, AFP, UPI - 21/07/09)
